Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.collection

Class EnumToIntMap<K extends Enum<K>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.common.collection.EnumToIntMap<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of the enum class
    public final class EnumToIntMap<K extends Enum<K>>
extends Object
    A fast enum-to-int Map implementation. The map is backed by a simple int array with the same length as the number of constants in the enum class. One integer must be designated to signify the absence of a key (i.e. an enum constant). By default this is Integer.MIN_VALUE. If an element in the int array has this value, it means there is no entry for the corresponding enum constant in the EnumToIntMap. It is not allowed to add a key with this value to the map, as is would in effect amount to removing that key from the map. It is also not allowed to pass this value to containsValue. In both cases an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman
